Here's my take: 
Miu is cheerful and hardworking, she is the traditional Idol, and as close as you can get to a Hololive member for spics, very influential for her kohais especially Misora and Rose.
Lia started out being similar to Miu with a spicy touch, but got tired of all the idol crap and decided to become the antithesis of an idol, Vulgar and Yabe she defines herself as a free spirit, basically doing whatever she wants.
I don't know Piyoko but according to Miu's comments, she is an extremely kind and helpful girl, willing to give advice to her colleagues on various topics. Lia respects her so much that she calls her sensei.
Hana is very shy and soft-spoken, she has a calm aura but she tends to panic easily when things don't go her way, she loves to dance and perform choreographies that fill her with energy "according to her".
I don't know anything about Rui besides being a trap and being a great singer.
Laila is outgoing and social, probably the one who is most willing to socialize outside of wactor. Very vocal on social media, she has a very infectious laugh and a very sultry voice and occasionally roasts her fans.
Suzu is organized and mature, but she is more focused on the Chinese audience than on spic, due to the little time she has in her daily life she only has time to do one or two streams a week on youtube.
Rose is tender and has a childish sense of humor, despite wanting to give an air of "Big Sister" in the end ends up giving the opposite result, she is also jealous with her fans and wants to be always in the center of their attention, even so she is very loved by her fans.
Misora is the "random girl" a Miu fangirl who got in thanks to her fluent Spanish and her ability to communicate and entertain with her antics, she is the most popular girl with the spics because she manages the same kind of zoomer humor even dragging people who normally don't consume vtubers.
Pal is easy to laugh with and adorable in her own way, she has an aura of imouto with her fans and makes you want to protect her, even though she tends to be a bit spicy and sadistic.
Luna has an extroverted character and wants to give a cool appearance, she knew how to win her public quickly thanks to this, she is more interested in being a gamer but surprisingly she is a great singer and once a week she does a karaoke to show it, besides being nice she can also get irritated easily and doesn't handle criticism very well.
Himari is very talented and friendly, possesses a calm and comfy almost maternal aura and tends to take things easy, can play several musical instruments including piano and ukulele, and has a sublime voice. Himari has the potential to be the best singer in Wactor because of this.
